cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel 3D human pose detector using deep-learning pose estimation methods. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the method can be used for ergonomic analyses and other pose-based assessments, which are relevant to robotics. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is another possibility as the paper discusses transforming fisheye perspectives to rectilinear views, which involves image processing and graphics techniques. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a potential category as the paper deals with panoramic cameras and stereo reconstruction, which are relevant to multimedia applications. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possibility as the paper discusses ergonomic analyses and pose-based assessments, which are relevant to human-computer interaction.
